 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from one or other of the numerous places called Marston or Merston, in counties including Bedfordshire, Cheshire, Derbyshire, Gloucestershire, Isle of Wight, Kent, Northamptonshire, Oxfordshire, Shropshire, Staffordshire, Sussex, and Worcestershire. Most of the placenames derive from Old English <i>mersc</i> ‘marsh’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’."],"variants":[{"name":"Marson","meanings":["English (Midlands): variant of   Marston  , a common placename which was often spelled and pronounced <i>Marson</i>.","French: habitational name from any of the places so called in Marne and Meuse, or from Marçon in Sarthe. This surname is also found in Germany."]},{"name":"Maston","meanings":["English: variant of   Marston   with loss of <i>-r-</i>."]}]},{"name":"Johannes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Johannes MARSTON was born in 1520, in Slawston, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas MARSTON, was 25 and his mother, Alice Allen Barrett, was 9. He had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Maria Turuile. He died in 1578, in Repps, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1520–1578":"1520–1578","1525–1588":"1525–1588","1522–1570":"1522–1570","1542–1603":"1542–1603","1548–1599":"1548–1599","1552–1647":"1552–1647","1555–Male":"1555–Surnud","1495–1549":"1495–1549","1511–1587":"1511–1587","1495":"1495","1570":"1570","1525":"1525","1578":"1578","1555":"1555","1511":"1511","1599":"1599","1522":"1522","1588":"1588","1587":"1587","1520":"1520","1542":"1542","1552":"1552","1549":"1549","1548":"1548","27 March 1549":"27. märts 1549","1647":"1647","1603":"1603","Slawston, Leicestershire,England":"Slawston, Leicestershire, Inglismaa,